    "summary": "BlueConic exposes two HTTP REST API surfaces: the current tenant-scoped REST API v2 using OAuth 2.0 bearer tokens, and a retired REST API v1 using OAuth 1.0a signed requests.",
    "description": "BlueConic is a customer data platform used to collect, unify, and act on customer profile, segment, interaction, and audit-event data. Its product documentation describes tenant-hosted REST APIs for accessing this data and managing application access.",
    "credentials": {
      "blueconic_oauth_app": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "BlueConic OAuth 2.0 application credentials (client ID and client secret)",
        "generateUrl": "https://support.blueconic.com/en/articles/247557-authorizing-applications-granting-external-applications-to-access-blueconic",
        "setup": "In BlueConic, go to [Authorizing Applications: Granting external applications to access BlueConic](https://support.blueconic.com/en/articles/247557-authorizing-applications-granting-external-applications-to-access-blueconic) and then in the product navigate to **Settings > Access management > Applications**. Click **Add an application**, choose either **Authorization code flow** or **Client credentials flow**, configure scopes and any IP allowlist, and save. BlueConic issues a `client_id` and `client_secret` when the application is saved; turn the application status **ON** before use."
      },
      "blueconic_oauth1_consumer": {
        "type": "signature",
        "label": "BlueConic REST API v1 OAuth 1.0a consumer key and consumer secret",
        "generateUrl": "https://support.blueconic.com/en/articles/248012-blueconic-rest-api-v1",
        "setup": "For the retired v1 API, BlueConic assigns a `Consumer Key` and `Consumer Secret` to each consumer/application and requests must be signed with OAuth `1.0a` using `HMAC-SHA1` in the request headers. See [BlueConic REST API v1](https://support.blueconic.com/en/articles/248012-blueconic-rest-api-v1). The article describes the credential pair and signing requirements, but the currently published page does not clearly document a current self-service minting screen for new v1 credentials because v1 is retired."
      }
    },
